# 6. 視点を変えれば

Ena: <Alright, this seems like a good place for me to stop today!>
Mizuki: <Yeah, I think I'll stop here too. I have work tomorrow, and it's been a little while since I last went.>
Kanade: <Okay. Thank you for your hard work, everyone.>
Mizuki: <Later♪>
Mafuyu: Are you going to keep working, Kanade...?
Kanade: Yes, I'd like to make a little more progress while I can.
Mafuyu: Okay. Good night...
Kanade: Good night, Mafuyu.
Kanade: Phew...
Kanade: Oh, a message...?
Kanade: (No, it's just a newsletter. I thought it was...)
Kanade: (I still haven't heard back from her...)
Kanade: I hope Tenma's okay...
Saki: I'm going to take another hard look at what I think makes you really shine, Kanade!
Saki: That might be the key to figuring out what I'm missing!
Kanade: (What if she's really struggling to find the answer?)
Kanade: (I said that I'd help her until the end, but I haven't been able to do anything for her...)
Kanade: This isn't good. I can't focus on my work at all...
Kanade: Maybe I should take a short break in SEKAI...
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: (There's someone over by the water...)
Kanade: Rin...?
Rin: Kanade? When did you get here...?
Kanade: Just now. I came to take a short break.
Rin: Your timing couldn't have been better.
Kanade: Huh?
Rin: ...
Rin: Is my brooch crooked at all...?
Rin: I tried using the water as a mirror, but I couldn't really tell...
Kanade: Umm... It looks straight to me.
Rin: Okay. That's good to hear.
Kanade: Your brooch is very pretty.
Rin: Mizuki found it at a shop, thought it would look good on me and decided to bring it over.
Rin: And I felt like wearing it today...
Kanade: I see. Mizuki would be so happy to hear that.
Rin: Yeah...
Rin: Do you wear any jewelry like this, Kanade?
Kanade: Huh?
Rin: Mizuki and the others said that you were modeling for someone.
Rin: Did you put on any jewelry during your shoot?
Kanade: Yes. Brooches, necklaces and a variety of other things.
Kanade: ...
Rin: Is something wrong?
Kanade: Oh, no... Nothing too serious. It's just...
Kanade: Things haven't been going so well.
Rin: Really...?
Kanade: *Nod* We did our shoot the other day...
Kanade: Tenma said that I possess the sort of radiance she's looking for...
Kanade: But we weren't able to fully capture that in any of the pictures we took. And that's bothering her...
Rin: Radiance...?
Kanade: *Nod* She said she's going to take another hard look at what that means to her.
Kanade: But I also understand that feeling that your piece is incomplete because you're missing something.
Kanade: I was hoping to help her somehow, but I really don't know what to do...
Rin: I see.
Kanade: *Nod* What would you do in this sort of situation, Rin...?
Rin: You can't expect me to immediately answer that question...
Kanade: Yes, of course. I'm sorry...
Rin: I wouldn't know what to do either...
Rin: This is like the opposite of how things usually go.
Kanade: The opposite...?
Rin: Yeah. Whenever you have trouble reaching someone with a song or don't know what you're trying to express to them...
Rin: You try to get to know that person, right?
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: You're right... When I first decided to try to compose a song that could save Mafuyu...
Kanade: I started by taking a closer look at what she was thinking and feeling...
Kanade: I did overstep a few times as a result...
Kanade: But I was also able to learn more about what's really going on with Mafuyu. I figured out what I wanted to do and channeled it into my songs...
Rin: Well, if you don't know, then you should go find out...
Rin: That can change things a lot, right?
Kanade: Rin...
Kanade: I see your point. This is sort of the opposite of how things usually go.
Kanade: Then...
Kanade: (I don't know if this will help Tenma find the right answer.)
Kanade: (But if I can give her even the smallest hint...)
Kanade: I really appreciate it, Rin.
Kanade: I think I know what to do now thanks to you.
Rin: Okay.
Rin: Let me know if the picture turns out. I wanna see...
Kanade: Okay. I'll bring it by once it's ready.
Rin: I'll be waiting...
